TY  - JOUR
T1  - Stealing Fire: Creative Deviance in the Evolution of New Ideas
AU  - Mainemelis, Charalampos
Y1  - 2010/10/01
PY  - 2010
DA  - 2010/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.35.4.zok558
DO  - 10.5465/amr.35.4.zok558
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 558
EP  - 578
VL  - 35
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - What happens when an employee generates a new idea and wants to further explore it but is instructed by a manager to stop working on it? Among the various possibilities, the employee could choose to violate the manager's order and pursue the new idea illegitimately. I describe this action as creative deviance and, drawing on the creativity literature and deviance literature, propose a theory about its organizational conditions and implications.
AB  - What happens when an employee generates a new idea and wants to further explore it but is instructed by a manager to stop working on it? Among the various possibilities, the employee could choose to violate the manager's order and pursue the new idea illegitimately. I describe this action as creative deviance and, drawing on the creativity literature and deviance literature, propose a theory about its organizational conditions and implications.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.35.4.zok558
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.35.4.zok558
Y2  - 2026/04/24
