TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Multidimensional Conceptualization of Environmental Velocity
AU  - McCarthy, Ian P.
AU  - Lawrence, Thomas B.
AU  - Wixted, Brian
AU  - Gordon, Brian R.
Y1  - 2010/10/01
PY  - 2010
DA  - 2010/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.35.4.zok604
DO  - 10.5465/amr.35.4.zok604
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 604
EP  - 626
VL  - 35
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Environmental velocity has emerged as an important concept but remains theoretically underdeveloped, particularly with respect to its multidimensionality. In response, we develop a framework that examines the variations in velocity across multiple dimensions of the environment (homology) and the causal linkages between those velocities (coupling). We then propose four velocity regimes based on different patterns of homology and coupling and argue that the conditions of each regime have important implications for organizations.
AB  - Environmental velocity has emerged as an important concept but remains theoretically underdeveloped, particularly with respect to its multidimensionality. In response, we develop a framework that examines the variations in velocity across multiple dimensions of the environment (homology) and the causal linkages between those velocities (coupling). We then propose four velocity regimes based on different patterns of homology and coupling and argue that the conditions of each regime have important implications for organizations.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.35.4.zok604
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.35.4.zok604
Y2  - 2026/04/24
